  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Pediatric Nutrition Monitor\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Pediatric Nutrition Monitor\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Tracks child nutrition adequacy, growth trajectory, and micronutrient status for children ages 0\u201312 in low- and medium-income home settings. Monitors growth percentile trends, caloric adequacy, iron/vitamin D/B12 micronutrient balance, and dietary diversity \u2014 the four dimensions most predictive of developmental outcomes in under-resourced households. Output at [2003:2007] feeds the Home Caregiver Burden Monitor, as child nutritional problems are a primary driver of caregiver stress and care coordination demand.\n\nPOPULATION: Children ages 0\u201312; WIC-eligible families; households with limited grocery access or food insecurity\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- growth_percentile_norm (index 0):  0.0 = <5th percentile (failure to thrive / significant underweight) | 0.5 = 25th\u201375th percentile (healthy range) | 1.0 = >95th percentile (overweight risk in low-income context)\n- caloric_adequacy_norm (index 1):  0.0 = severe caloric deficit (<50% daily requirement) | 0.5 = adequate (90\u2013110% daily requirement) | 1.0 = consistent surplus\n- micronutrient_score_norm (index 2):  0.0 = multiple confirmed deficiencies (Fe, Vit D, B12 all low) | 0.5 = borderline adequate | 1.0 = well-supplemented across all tracked nutrients\n- dietary_diversity_norm (index 3):  0.0 = single food group only (calorie-dense, low-nutrient) | 0.5 = moderate variety (3+ food groups) | 1.0 = high diversity (5+ food groups consistently)\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- GROWTH_ALERT (RED) -> action: WIC referral; pediatrician growth review; food prescription program screening\n- MICRONUTRIENT_CONCERN (AMBER) -> action: Lab screening referral; WIC food package review; supplement prescription; dietitian consult\n- NUTRITION_OK (GREEN) -> action: Caregiver burden monitor registers healthy child nutrition state",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "growth_percentile_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "<5th percentile (failure to thrive / significant underweight)",
          "mid": "25th\u201375th percentile (healthy range)",
          "high": ">95th percentile (overweight risk in low-income context)"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "caloric_adequacy_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "severe caloric deficit (<50% daily requirement)",
          "mid": "adequate (90\u2013110% daily requirement)",
          "high": "consistent surplus"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "micronutrient_score_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "multiple confirmed deficiencies (Fe, Vit D, B12 all low)",
          "mid": "borderline adequate",
          "high": "well-supplemented across all tracked nutrients"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "dietary_diversity_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "single food group only (calorie-dense, low-nutrient)",
          "mid": "moderate variety (3+ food groups)",
          "high": "high diversity (5+ food groups consistently)"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "ped-nut-growth-faltering",
        "label": "GROWTH_ALERT",
        "rag": "RED",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "WIC referral; pediatrician growth review; food prescription program screening"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "ped-nut-micronutrient",
        "label": "MICRONUTRIENT_CONCERN",
        "rag": "AMBER",
        "outputIndex": 2,
        "action": "Lab screening referral; WIC food package review; supplement prescription; dietitian consult"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "ped-nut-ok",
        "label": "NUTRITION_OK",
        "rag": "GREEN",
        "outputIndex": 3,
        "action": "Caregiver burden monitor registers healthy child nutrition state"
      }
    ]
  },
